sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI+luxR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoter (lambda cI and luxR regulated -- hybrid)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
cI repressor negatively regulates this promoter and LuxR activates its transcription.The effect of cI is dominant over LuxR. This part is based on the LuxR and cI repressor regulated hybrid promoter designed and tested by Ron Weiss. It requires the binding of two cI repressor dimers for maximal repression and contains two cI repressor binding sites namely, OR1 and OR2. This promoter is leaky in the sense that 'some' transcription is seen in the absence of both cI and LuxR.

 

LuxI cI activity of promoter
+ + zero
+ - maximum
- + zero
- - leaky (no quantitative information)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part was designed based on the LuxR and cI repressor regulated hybrid promoter tested by Ron Weiss and the LuxR-LuxICDABE sequence annotated by Tom Knight AF170104.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K584029
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a basic biobrick we made for our project. We performed a PCR to get the CeaB part of the K131009 biobrick. The primer design for this was such that it already contained the ribolock resulting in ???Ribolock + ceaB??? as the final product. This is fused with the terminator B0015 to get ???Ribolock + ceaB + B0015???.
Therefore ???Ribolock + ceaB + B0015??? is a basic buildig block.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bakul Jitendra Vinchhi, Sarah Veugelen, Katrien Vandermeeren, Yana Hoorne
